1
00:00:00,420 --> 00:00:02,520
The 1st Gaki no Tsukai Arahende chikichiki

2
00:00:02,600 --> 00:00:06,320
Dance until you spread on social media~!!

3
00:00:08,060 --> 00:00:10,240
Well...

4
00:00:10,240 --> 00:00:13,660
is everyone aware of the temperature outside?

5
00:00:13,660 --> 00:00:20,140
It's a nice day today.
- Yes, it's easily over 95°F. The heat is really intense!

6
00:00:20,600 --> 00:00:22,540
Regarding today's plan...

7
00:00:22,540 --> 00:00:26,300
let's go around drinking delicious iced-coffee around town.

8
00:00:26,780 --> 00:00:29,900
That's drastically different from what was said.

9
00:00:29,900 --> 00:00:32,400
"Dance until you spread on social media."
- Oh is that so?

10
00:00:32,400 --> 00:00:36,140
I didn't get a chance to communicate with the staff.

11
00:00:36,160 --> 00:00:38,000
Get that part right.

12
00:00:38,740 --> 00:00:44,440
Things spread on social media so fast. So-and-so did this. So-and-so did that.

13
00:00:44,440 --> 00:00:46,960
And we won't be playing against each other, but...

14
00:00:46,960 --> 00:00:51,040
right now, one-by-one, we'll dance somewhere in public.

15
00:00:51,840 --> 00:00:55,720
And you can't stop until you get on social media.

16
00:01:06,080 --> 00:01:10,660
Rule 1: With no visible film crew, dance by yourself in the park.

17
00:01:10,820 --> 00:01:15,200
Rule 2: Until someone tweets about it, you can't stop.

18
00:01:16,120 --> 00:01:19,700
But today is a heat wave above 104°F!

19
00:01:19,700 --> 00:01:25,520
Ueno Park as the stage, the curtains open up to a harsh environment.

20
00:01:25,840 --> 00:01:27,580
These are the dances.

21
00:01:28,445 --> 00:01:29,765
There's lots.

22
00:01:30,820 --> 00:01:34,580
Tako Dance...they have to mention the dance too.

23
00:01:34,580 --> 00:01:37,260
"Endo is doing the Para Para."

24
00:01:37,800 --> 00:01:39,855
So it has to have those two words.

25
00:01:39,855 --> 00:01:42,485
It's about 2:30, right now.

26
00:01:42,485 --> 00:01:45,340
The temperature is going up and up.

27
00:01:45,560 --> 00:01:47,600
Let's finish this quck.

28
00:01:48,280 --> 00:01:50,940
What should we do about the order?

29
00:01:52,000 --> 00:01:54,380
One-by-one, right?

30
00:01:54,380 --> 00:01:56,380
Let the young guys go first.

31
00:01:56,820 --> 00:01:58,660
We're not that young though.

32
00:01:59,900 --> 00:02:01,740
We're 47.

33
00:02:02,180 --> 00:02:03,980
This is Japan now.

34
00:02:07,580 --> 00:02:11,300
With that, the young, Tanaka attempts.

35
00:02:11,640 --> 00:02:12,980
His dance is?

36
00:02:13,420 --> 00:02:16,380
When you think Tanaka, you think "Loach Scoop".

37
00:02:17,960 --> 00:02:20,420
So Loach Scoop? I understand.

38
00:02:20,420 --> 00:02:22,260
Better not pretend to faint.

39
00:02:23,040 --> 00:02:26,760
If you're gonna fall, fall forward. Backwards is fainting.

40
00:02:29,260 --> 00:02:32,420
(Ueno Park in front of the water fountain)
- Where is he at?

41
00:02:34,100 --> 00:02:36,720
Ahh! He's walking. Left. Left.

42
00:02:37,380 --> 00:02:39,620
No one's following with cameras so...

43
00:02:39,780 --> 00:02:43,860
it looks like Tanaka's private time.

44
00:02:44,180 --> 00:02:47,060
Tanaka does a solid job.

45
00:02:47,100 --> 00:02:48,140
Chopsticks.

46
00:02:48,500 --> 00:02:52,120
Do that and carry that.

47
00:02:52,900 --> 00:02:54,000
Let's go!!

48
00:02:56,060 --> 00:02:57,960
The chopsticks...

49
00:02:58,380 --> 00:03:02,900
might make it harder to recognize that it's Tanaka.

50
00:03:03,740 --> 00:03:05,880
Maybe he shouldn't have used them.

51
00:03:06,120 --> 00:03:10,520
This is bad. They think he's weird so nobody wants to get closer.

52
00:03:11,100 --> 00:03:14,140
They're watching and laughing from afar.

53
00:03:14,300 --> 00:03:17,180
I mean, if that was there, would you go?

54
00:03:19,260 --> 00:03:20,680
Some sightseers...

55
00:03:21,080 --> 00:03:22,620
are doing something.

56
00:03:23,260 --> 00:03:24,320
Just passing through.

57
00:03:27,000 --> 00:03:29,440
A lot of tourists!
- This is bad!

58
00:03:29,900 --> 00:03:31,600
Your movements are too slow.

59
00:03:31,600 --> 00:03:33,960
You don't look like your scooping loaches.

60
00:03:33,960 --> 00:03:35,540
Cleaner.

61
00:03:36,100 --> 00:03:37,120
Do it for real!

62
00:03:38,400 --> 00:03:40,180
Yea, yea, yea...

63
00:03:42,360 --> 00:03:44,080
You'll pass out in 10 minutes.

64
00:03:47,400 --> 00:03:49,460
You're not showing up at all.

65
00:03:50,500 --> 00:03:52,700
Not showing up at all?

66
00:03:53,780 --> 00:03:56,120
Please, hurry up.

67
00:03:57,040 --> 00:03:58,820
How many loaches did you catch?

68
00:03:58,820 --> 00:04:00,300
Right now, I caught 3.

69
00:04:00,300 --> 00:04:01,540
Caught 3, did ya?

70
00:04:02,020 --> 00:04:02,980
That's a lot!

71
00:04:06,340 --> 00:04:09,620
It's been 10 minutes.
- It has been 10 minutes.

72
00:04:12,820 --> 00:04:14,300
This is a disaster.

73
00:04:14,760 --> 00:04:16,100
Nothing's showing up.

74
00:04:16,615 --> 00:04:17,615
Is that so?

75
00:04:18,380 --> 00:04:21,020
What do you wanna do?
- It's cus no one's watching.

76
00:04:21,020 --> 00:04:24,800
There isn't even a tweet regarding Tanaka, is there?

77
00:04:24,800 --> 00:04:27,320
Oh he's doing something.

78
00:04:27,540 --> 00:04:28,600
Is he waving?

79
00:04:30,460 --> 00:04:31,995
They just came to look.

80
00:04:32,000 --> 00:04:34,060
But maybe he...

81
00:04:35,140 --> 00:04:40,260
inputted to them that Tanaka is loach scooping so.

82
00:04:40,720 --> 00:04:42,760
But they just nodded and left.

83
00:04:43,040 --> 00:04:44,840
I wonder what they're thinking.

84
00:04:47,440 --> 00:04:49,240
This is tough.

85
00:04:52,140 --> 00:04:53,880
Wanna bring him back?
- Bring him back.

86
00:04:53,880 --> 00:04:55,620
Tanaka, wanna come back one time?

87
00:04:56,040 --> 00:04:57,040
This is impossible.

88
00:04:57,420 --> 00:04:59,000
I'll come back.
[Challenge Time 15:16]

89
00:05:00,340 --> 00:05:01,780
How is it?

90
00:05:02,280 --> 00:05:03,840
No, nothing.

91
00:05:04,160 --> 00:05:06,600
Nothing.
- Not even "Cocorico Tanaka".

92
00:05:07,100 --> 00:05:08,800
He's back.

93
00:05:09,760 --> 00:05:10,620
Nice job.

94
00:05:10,880 --> 00:05:12,540
How was it?

95
00:05:12,935 --> 00:05:14,675
Um...

96
00:05:15,900 --> 00:05:17,260
It doesn't matter how long.

97
00:05:18,060 --> 00:05:19,280
You're sweating.

98
00:05:19,820 --> 00:05:21,580
We were all saying...

99
00:05:22,140 --> 00:05:24,020
another hour and it'll be good.

100
00:05:25,180 --> 00:05:26,880
No way!

101
00:05:27,160 --> 00:05:28,880
No way. I'll pass out before then.

102
00:05:29,420 --> 00:05:30,820
Let's try someone else.

103
00:05:30,820 --> 00:05:33,640
Please, please. Someone else go.

104
00:05:34,460 --> 00:05:35,360
Shall we go Emperor!

105
00:05:35,455 --> 00:05:38,295
Who? Who's goin?
- Emperor!

106
00:05:38,340 --> 00:05:40,160
Ahh! Dahama-san, right?

107
00:05:43,380 --> 00:05:45,960
If it doesn't work here for Dahama-san, then it's impossible.

108
00:05:45,960 --> 00:05:50,000
That's right! If it's impossible for Downtown then it's impossible.

109
00:05:51,560 --> 00:05:53,460
Next challenger is Hamada

110
00:05:53,640 --> 00:05:55,980
His selected dance is?

111
00:05:56,480 --> 00:05:57,700
I can do the Twist.

112
00:06:00,725 --> 00:06:01,725
Ehhh?

113
00:06:02,360 --> 00:06:05,400
This feels super exhausting.

114
00:06:05,680 --> 00:06:07,260
The familiar the dance, the better.

115
00:06:07,880 --> 00:06:09,520
They'll know what the Twist is.

116
00:06:09,620 --> 00:06:10,880
Please, Hamada-san!

117
00:06:13,720 --> 00:06:14,880
Already...

118
00:06:15,360 --> 00:06:20,120
while on standby, a guy recognized him...

119
00:06:20,380 --> 00:06:22,120
