120
00:06:23,420 --> 00:06:24,560
That guy, right?

121
00:06:24,640 --> 00:06:26,520
He's taking pictures!

122
00:06:30,340 --> 00:06:31,540
It started!

123
00:06:31,640 --> 00:06:33,640
He does the Twist fast.

124
00:06:34,100 --> 00:06:35,740
Was the Twist that fast?

125
00:06:36,435 --> 00:06:39,195
Even the Twist experts don't go that fast.

126
00:06:41,040 --> 00:06:42,760
They're coming!

127
00:06:45,380 --> 00:06:48,400
Wow, you're right! Incredible!

128
00:06:48,840 --> 00:06:50,420
Agh! Did he pull his back?

129
00:06:52,520 --> 00:06:54,480
What's wrong?
- He probably pulled his back.

130
00:06:54,580 --> 00:06:55,580
What's wrong?

131
00:06:56,820 --> 00:06:57,820
Tired.

132
00:07:00,900 --> 00:07:04,760
You're getting a lot of attention, Hamada! Nice, nice, nice...

133
00:07:04,760 --> 00:07:07,860
You're doing good. Keep twisting.

134
00:07:08,340 --> 00:07:09,260
Lookin good!

135
00:07:14,200 --> 00:07:15,200
Hard breathing.

136
00:07:18,360 --> 00:07:20,140
Is he dying?

137
00:07:22,820 --> 00:07:25,480
Nothing's coming up.
- It's too hot!

138
00:07:35,060 --> 00:07:37,420
Staff, go check on him.

139
00:07:37,420 --> 00:07:38,700
IT'S HOT!

140
00:07:39,240 --> 00:07:42,300
It is hot. Let's hang in there!

141
00:07:42,300 --> 00:07:47,480
[Hama-chan, started something shitty yesterday so I wanna kill him.]

142
00:07:50,140 --> 00:07:53,220
Maybe it's a different Hama-chan.

143
00:07:55,000 --> 00:07:59,580
Maybe Hamada got into road rage with somebody and now he wants to kill him.

144
00:07:59,600 --> 00:08:01,140
It's a different Hamada-san.
- You think?

145
00:08:02,760 --> 00:08:04,500
And just then!

146
00:08:06,880 --> 00:08:08,580
We got something!

147
00:08:08,880 --> 00:08:11,700
[Found Hama-chan at Ueno Park.]

148
00:08:13,180 --> 00:08:17,060
Yes, yes, yes...
- We just need the "Twist"!

149
00:08:17,180 --> 00:08:18,800
Do the Twist!

150
00:08:23,360 --> 00:08:25,660
He's not moving so good.

151
00:08:27,720 --> 00:08:29,360
It's not a big deal.

152
00:08:29,360 --> 00:08:32,540
Shall we bring him back?
- Yeah. He almost had it.

153
00:08:32,540 --> 00:08:34,440
Come back, one time.
[Challenge Time 10:43]

154
00:08:34,780 --> 00:08:35,780
But...

155
00:08:35,980 --> 00:08:38,180
But there was a tweet.

156
00:08:39,720 --> 00:08:41,120
Whoa! So much sweat!

157
00:08:41,120 --> 00:08:41,860
Not bad.

158
00:08:43,480 --> 00:08:44,520
So much sweat!

159
00:08:46,920 --> 00:08:48,900
Did you cover yourself in water?

160
00:08:49,660 --> 00:08:50,660
Why would I?

161
00:08:51,880 --> 00:08:53,460
It's dizzying.

162
00:08:53,660 --> 00:08:56,060
We can't do this! We can't do this!

163
00:08:56,060 --> 00:08:57,480
Is this what it's like!?

164
00:08:57,740 --> 00:08:59,780
You look varnished!

165
00:09:01,580 --> 00:09:02,660
Varnish.

166
00:09:03,200 --> 00:09:04,340
He's so shiny.

167
00:09:04,340 --> 00:09:06,680
You're a woodworker's finished product!

168
00:09:07,960 --> 00:09:10,980
You had a close one.
- Oh really?

169
00:09:10,980 --> 00:09:14,160
[Found Hama-chan at Ueno Park. On location??]

170
00:09:15,460 --> 00:09:17,080
No "Twist" though!

171
00:09:17,080 --> 00:09:18,640
What's this, "shitty"?

172
00:09:19,880 --> 00:09:23,840
[Hama-chan, started something shitty yesterday so I wanna kill him.]

173
00:09:25,080 --> 00:09:28,720
Did you start something yesterday?
- Why would I do something like that.

174
00:09:28,720 --> 00:09:31,320
How do you know it's me?

175
00:09:31,760 --> 00:09:34,360
Well, Hama-chan could be anybody.

176
00:09:35,340 --> 00:09:37,640
Maybe they're talking about Nishida Toshiyuki.

177
00:09:42,260 --> 00:09:44,200
The Twist was no good, huh?

178
00:09:44,360 --> 00:09:45,940
Isn't it time for that?

179
00:09:45,940 --> 00:09:49,020
Let's get one with Shozo. With that flashy...

180
00:09:50,100 --> 00:09:51,620
The Samba, right?

181
00:09:51,620 --> 00:09:54,240
All out Samba!
- Samba?

182
00:09:54,700 --> 00:09:55,580
It's flashy.

183
00:09:56,600 --> 00:09:59,500
Next, Endo attempts with the Samba!

184
00:09:59,580 --> 00:10:01,800
Will he get tweeted!?

185
00:10:02,600 --> 00:10:06,900
(Ueno Park in front of the Tokyo Metropolitan Art Museum 93.9°F)

186
00:10:06,900 --> 00:10:09,120
He's a man who knows the Samba.

187
00:10:11,240 --> 00:10:12,820
I think Endo will do it.

188
00:10:19,260 --> 00:10:20,600
There he goes.

189
00:10:23,680 --> 00:10:27,700
Nice, nice. It's the Samba.

190
00:10:35,380 --> 00:10:37,720
Can he keep this up?

191
00:10:44,220 --> 00:10:46,480
Is this the rhythm of the Samba?

192
00:10:46,485 --> 00:10:48,615
It's working.

193
00:10:52,600 --> 00:10:53,880
What happened?

194
00:10:56,685 --> 00:10:57,685
What's wrong?

195
00:10:58,745 --> 00:11:01,425
How bout her?

196
00:11:02,595 --> 00:11:05,685
Is that her cellphone? Did she take a picture?

197
00:11:05,920 --> 00:11:06,880
Endo, what's wrong?

198
00:11:06,880 --> 00:11:08,160
It's hot!

199
00:11:08,580 --> 00:11:09,900
It's hot!

200
00:11:10,000 --> 00:11:11,300
It's not that hot!

201
00:11:11,560 --> 00:11:12,800
It's super hot.

202
00:11:13,800 --> 00:11:14,920
You're fine.

203
00:11:15,260 --> 00:11:16,860
There's no sense of the Samba.

204
00:11:16,860 --> 00:11:17,700
Really?

205
00:11:18,100 --> 00:11:20,100
It feels like Samba here.

206
00:11:20,600 --> 00:11:21,960
Smile more.

207
00:11:22,860 --> 00:11:24,280
Like you're having fun time.

208
00:11:24,860 --> 00:11:26,240
I'll show more fun.

209
00:11:32,840 --> 00:11:34,120
Nice! Nice!

210
00:11:39,760 --> 00:11:41,440
What's this rhythm?

211
00:11:41,740 --> 00:11:43,140
I've never heard of this rhythm.

212
00:11:50,245 --> 00:11:53,205
Endo reaches the limit of his all-out Samba.

213
00:11:54,000 --> 00:11:55,000
And then!

214
00:12:01,360 --> 00:12:07,120
[Cocorico's Endo is at Ueno Park with feathers and dancing the Samba.]

215
00:12:07,880 --> 00:12:08,880
YES~!

216
00:12:12,860 --> 00:12:13,820
Thank you very much!

217
00:12:16,440 --> 00:12:19,420
Man, I'm tired.

218
00:12:21,420 --> 00:12:24,220
I wonder who it was.
- I have no idea.

219
00:12:24,220 --> 00:12:26,800
Probably a college girl.

220
00:12:26,800 --> 00:12:28,180
Amazing, Endo.

221
00:12:28,800 --> 00:12:29,380
Except...

222
00:12:32,120 --> 00:12:32,920
