225
00:12:38,945 --> 00:12:42,285
It's the Ippon Manzoku.

226
00:12:44,645 --> 00:12:46,795
Maybe that came out.

227
00:12:47,540 --> 00:12:50,520
So who's next?
- Ain't that you?

228
00:12:50,520 --> 00:12:51,560
Shall we?

229
00:12:51,920 --> 00:12:52,980
Of course it is.

230
00:12:53,385 --> 00:12:56,815
That's fine. I'll do it. But there aren't any more dances.

231
00:12:56,935 --> 00:13:00,085
Do Wotagei.
- Wotagei?

232
00:13:00,085 --> 00:13:01,925
I've never done that.

233
00:13:02,415 --> 00:13:05,025
I've never done it.

234
00:13:08,980 --> 00:13:10,380
No "dying" out there.

235
00:13:11,740 --> 00:13:12,560
None of that.

236
00:13:12,580 --> 00:13:14,380
He just falls back.

237
00:13:15,580 --> 00:13:17,380
No "dying" and running away?

238
00:13:21,820 --> 00:13:24,220
If you please!

239
00:13:24,720 --> 00:13:25,720
Wotagei.

240
00:13:26,900 --> 00:13:29,460
(Ueno Park National Science Museum 93.6°F)

241
00:13:29,460 --> 00:13:30,520
Here he comes.

242
00:13:31,400 --> 00:13:33,160
There's people in front.

243
00:13:34,660 --> 00:13:37,700
He's already getting attention.

244
00:13:41,700 --> 00:13:43,000
They gave him something.

245
00:13:44,440 --> 00:13:45,780
Pen lights.

246
00:13:47,200 --> 00:13:49,560
Oh fast.
